			<sentence id="4.3">in most recent window"</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.4">2 open web page</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.5">3 click on link which brings a new window with hidden toolbar</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.6">4 open another web page</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.7">5 click on link which brings a new window with hidden toolbar</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">Actual Results:  
most recent window has two tabs but they are hidden and first page is not
accessible.</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.2">(if tab would not created then there is a Back in context menu to
bring previous page)</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">Expected Results:  
I think if toolbar in most recent window is hidden then browser must open a new
window rather then hide current page in most recent window.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
